Sorting Lab¶

Q1. Implement Bubble Sort with the idea that if there are no exchanges in a particular pass (round), then the sort terminates.¶

Q2. Implement Selection Sort.¶

Q3. Implement Insertion Sort with the idea that the location of the next element in the sorted portion is found using binary search.¶

Q4. Create best cases and worst cases for both sorts above and compare their timings.¶

Q5. Implement Mergesort Algorithm.¶

Q6. Implement Quicksort algorithm where the pivot is always the middle element.¶

Q7. Implement Quicksort algorithm where the pivot is chosen randomly.¶

Q8. Implement Radixsort Algorithm.¶
